      <hedline>
        <hl1>Off to Be the Wizard</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Photo of Daniel Radcliffe, who will star as schoolboy wizard in film version of Harry Potter book series by Warner Brothers, with Emma Watson and Rupert Grint, who will play Hermione and Ron</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Daniel Radcliffe, 11, center, who will star as the schoolboy wizard in a Harry Potter film from Warner Brothers, was introduced at a news conference yesterday in London with Emma Watson, 10, left, and Rupert Grint, 11, who will play Hermione and Ron. (Reuters)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Daniel Radcliffe, 11, center, who will star as the schoolboy wizard in a Harry Potter film from Warner Brothers, was introduced at a news conference yesterday in London with Emma Watson, 10, left, and Rupert Grint, 11, who will play Hermione and Ron. (Reuters)</p>
